ow is that admission to our undergraduate programs is handled through UIC’s main undergraduate admissions office —so we encourage you to visit its site if you have not already done so. If you are looking for information on how and when to apply, details on financial aid, and a link to the online application, that is where you will find it.  We invite you to use the menus above and the featured links below to learn more about electrical and computer engineering at the University of Illinois at Chicago.      second row of link options           Computer engineering major  Learn more about a program designed to help you bring new computing technologies into being.             Electrical engineering major  Find out how a UIC engineering education can prepare you to deal with massive power systems to tiny circuits.             Engineering physics major  Put yourself on the forefront of research and development with a fusion of math, science, and engineering.          first row of link options           The College  Electrical and computer engineering students belong to UIC’s College of Engineering. Explore our main College site.             UIC admissions  This is where you can get all the information you need about application procedures—and apply.             EE and CE overview  The advantages of our EE and CE majors—in two brief pages.           ABET Accreditation   The undergraduate programs in electrical engineering and computer engineering at UIC have been accredited since 2001 by ABET, the Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology , and its predecessor organizations. The department is in the process of applying for ABET accreditation for the engineering physics program, in line with a national trend of engineering schools beginning to seek ABET status for such programs.  ABET is the recognized accreditor for college and university programs in applied science, computing, engineering, and technology. It is a federation of 28 professional and technical societies representing these fields. Among the most respected accreditation organizations in the United States, ABET has provided leadership and quality assurance in higher education for more than 75 years.  Learn more about ABET accreditation at UIC ECE.      Learn more about  applying to UIC          Undergraduate    Back to main content           Admitted Students    Admissions    Accreditation    CE Major    EE Major    EP Major    Courses    Internships and Jobs    Minors    Student Groups    Student Profiles    Student Resources                   UIC Logo         College Of  Engineering           Quicklinks    Contact Us    Open Positions    Faculty Resources    Graduate Resources    Undergraduate Resources    ABET Accreditation         Contact   Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering  851 S. Morgan St., 1020 SEO, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3423  Fax: (312) 996-6465  ecestudentaffairs@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 